Sentencas: This study presents a numerical investigation on the proton exchange membrane fuel cell (PEMFC) and the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC), using the aerothermal and electrochemistry equations to describe all phenomena included in both types of the fuel cells.
Titulo: Computational parametric analysis of fuel cells: Application to PEMFC and SOFC

Sentencas: The computational process is based on the implementation of the mathematical fuel cells models in FLUENT computational fluid dynamics code.
Titulo: Computational parametric analysis of fuel cells: Application to PEMFC and SOFC

Sentencas: This is in order to evaluate the temperature field, the production of the electricity, and the distribution of the water mass fraction in different region of the fuel cells.
Titulo: Computational parametric analysis of fuel cells: Application to PEMFC and SOFC

Sentencas: The obtained results show that the simulation is able to evaluate the physical and chemical parameters to explain the main phenomena in the fuel cells.
